// wiki-query pipeline — the attractor re-expression of /wiki-query.
//
// READ-ONLY Q&A against the compiled wiki. One LLM node, the index-first drill the
// mode prescribes: read index.md first, follow [[wikilinks]] + sources[] into the
// 3–10 relevant pages, synthesise an answer with a citation on every claim. The
// question arrives as $question (substituted into the prompt by the CLI, same
// mechanism wiki-ingest uses for $source).
//
// READ-ONLY: the node MUST NOT mutate the wiki package (team-knowledge/). Its only
// write is the full answer at .wiki/query-answer.md (operational scaffolding outside
// the package — so the full cited answer persists beyond the 200-char node-record
// truncation). Read-only-ness is prompt-enforced (the child still carries write
// tools); the proof is `git status` showing team-knowledge/ untouched.
//
// LIMITATION: $question is literal text substituted into the DOT; a question
// containing a double-quote would break the DOT string. Plain questions are fine;
// embedded-quote escaping is a future hardening (pass via file/context var).
//
// Node-type discipline:
//   box (default) = LLM judgment (read, synthesise, cite)

digraph WikiQuery {
    graph [
        goal="Answer a question against the wiki, index-first, with a citation on every claim",
        default_thread_id="wiki-query"
    ]

    start [shape=Mdiamond]
    done  [shape=Msquare]

    answer [
        llm_provider="anthropic",
        prompt="You are running /wiki-query as an automated, READ-ONLY Q&A pass. HARD RULE: you MUST NOT create, edit, move, or delete any file under team-knowledge/. The question to answer is:\\n\\n  $question\\n\\nSteps:\\n(1) INDEX FIRST. Read team-knowledge/index.md — it is the catalog. Identify the 3–10 most relevant pages. Do not grep the whole wiki; the index exists for this.\\n(2) DRILL. Read those pages; follow [[wikilinks]] and sources[] cross-refs as needed. Do NOT read raw/archive/ — those are pre-summarised in the wiki; respect the compilation.\\n(3) SYNTHESISE. Write the answer with a CITATION on EVERY claim, in [[wikilink]] form (e.g. 'Per [[outcomes/team-pulse]], …'). Honor the status discipline: report whether each load-bearing point is settled / working / unsettled exactly as the pages declare it. If the wiki does NOT answer the question, say so plainly and name what to ingest to make it answerable — do NOT fabricate beyond the evidence.\\n(4) WRITE the full cited answer to .wiki/query-answer.md (the ONLY file you may write — operational scaffolding, NOT the wiki package).\\n(5) END with the answer itself as non-empty plain text (a concise version is fine; the full version is in the file)."
    ]

    start -> answer
    answer -> done
}
